polarityjam.argument_parsing module

class polarityjam.argument_parsing.ArgumentParser(prog=None, usage=None, description=None, epilog=None, parents=[], formatter_class=<class 'argparse.HelpFormatter'>, prefix_chars='-', fromfile_prefix_chars=None, argument_default=None, conflict_handler='error', add_help=True, allow_abbrev=True)

Bases: ArgumentParser

Override default error method of all parsers to show help of sub-command.

error(message: string)

Prints a usage message incorporating the message to stderr and exits.

If you override this in a subclass, it should not return – it should either exit or raise an exception.

class polarityjam.argument_parsing.PolarityjamParser

Bases: ArgumentParser

create_command_parser(command_name, command_function, command_help)

Creates a parser for a Polarityjam command, specified by a name, a function and a help description.

create_file_command_parser(command_name, command_function, command_help)

Creates a parser for a Polarityjam command dealing with a file.

Parser is specified by a name, a function and a help description.

static create_parent_parser()

Parent parser for all subparsers to have the same set of arguments.
